gredients from the stock fluxes given in Book VII under the same term. The method of
preparation, no doubt, dehydrated this one; it would, however, be quite effective for its
purpose of sulphurizing the copper. There is a compound given in the <I>Probierb&uuml;chlein</I> identical
with this, and it was probably Agricola's source of information.</note>
